  "content_markdown": "Version: 8.2Service tools\nOn this page\nAdd support mailboxes to Creatio to accelerate communication with your customers:\n* Creatio will register new cases automatically based on the incoming emails.\n* Customers will receive case notifications.\n* All case emails will be saved to the case history.\n## Add a support mailbox [](https://academy.creatio.com#title-2115-1)\u200b\nImportant\nBefore you begin, set up one or more mailboxes to use for case registration. Instructions: [Configure a shared mailbox](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1867).\n1. Click the ![](https://academy.creatio.com/docs/sites/en/files/images/Composable_apps/CaseManagement/btn_system_designer_new.png) button to **open the System Designer**.\n2. Go to the \"System setup\" block \u2192 \" **Lookups**.\"\n3. **Open** the **List of mailboxes for case registration** lookup.\n4. **Click New**.\n5. **Select the support mailbox** added during the [email integration setup](https://academy.creatio.com/node/189/) in the **Mailbox** field. The field is required.\n6. **Specify the name of the mailbox** you use to receive emails in the **Mailbox alias** field. Fill out the field only if you receive emails in the mailbox that differs from the mailbox you set up originally.\n7. **Specify the relevant category** in the **Case category** field. For example, \"Incident.\" The field is required.\n8. **Enter the mailbox description** in the **Description** field.\n9. **Select the language** Creatio will use for the email if the mailbox language selection rule is triggered in the **Message language** field. Learn more: [Set up the language of the support mailbox](https://academy.creatio.com#title-2115-2).\n10. Select the **Always use the mailbox language** checkbox to **send emails in the specified language regardless of other rules** (Fig. 1).\n11. **Repeat** steps 4\u201311 if you are using more than one support mailbox.\nFig. 1 Set up the support mailbox language\n![Fig.\u00a01 Set up the support mailbox language](https://academy.creatio.com/docs/sites/en/files/images/Service_Tools/case_settings/service_mailbox.png)\n**As a result** , Creatio will process all emails received by the mailboxes in the case registration system.\nYou can also set up a shared support mailbox for communicating with customers and sending case notifications. Learn more: [Configure a shared mailbox](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1867).\n## Send localized notifications [](https://academy.creatio.com#title-2115-2)\u200b\nCreatio enables you to send email notifications in the client's preferred language. To do this:\n1. Specify preferred language on the contact page.\n2. Localize email notifications templates. Instructions: [Set up template localization](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=2357&anchor=title-2116-4)\n3. Set up the mailbox language.\nIn Creatio, you can set up the language for:\n* the case notification mailbox\n* the email notification template\n* the notifications sent to customers who do not have the preferred language specified\nCreatio determines the email language based on the following rules:\n* If you **do not select** the **Always use the mailbox language** checkbox during the [email setup](https://academy.creatio.com#title-2115-1), Creatio uses the following variables to determine the language, from highest to lowest priority:\n* The preferred language of the recipient contact.\n* The email language specified during the mailbox setup.\n* The value of the \"Default language for messages\" (\"DefaultMessageLanguage\" code) system setting.\n* If you **select** the **Always use the mailbox language** checkbox, Creatio sends emails in the mailbox language regardless of other rules.\n* * *\n## See also\u200b\n[Set up the Microsoft Exchange and Microsoft 365 services](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1418)\n[Add IMAP/SMTP email provider](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1415)\n[Configure a shared mailbox](https://academy.creatio.com/documents?id=1867)\n* * *\n## Resources\u200b\n[Service cases](https://academy.creatio.com/node/531197/takecourse)",
